HEADWORD: Wheel-shaped
<hw>Wheel"-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Shaped like a wheel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Expanding into a flat, circular
border at top, with scarcely any tube; <as>as, a <ex>wheel-shaped</ex>
corolla</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wheelswarf</ent>⟦br⟧
